Message.MsgText: node.speed.property.value.invalid=XNMI0011E: The "{0}" custom property value is not of the correct format. Default value of {1} is used instead.
Message.Explanation: A value other than a floating point number is specified as the custom property value.
Message.UserResponse: Specify a floating point number as the value for the custom property.

Message.MsgText: named.unmanaged.node.not.found=XNMI0015E: There is no node with name "{0}" in cell "{2}". No statistics will be reported by the node.
Message.Explanation: The node custom property of a Generic Server Cluster endpoint specifies a node that is not defined in the specified cell.
Message.UserResponse: Either remove or correct the node name in the node custom property of the Generic Server Cluster endpoint or define a node with that name in the specified cell.

Message.MsgText: node.speed.invalid=XNMI0001E: NodeSpeed "{0}" received from remote agent is not of the correct format. Default value of {1} is used instead.
Message.Explanation: A value other than a floating point number is received from the remote agent as the nodeSpeed.
Message.UserResponse: If the remote agent is supplied by IBM, report the error to IBM support.

Message.MsgText: number.of.cpus.property.value.invalid=XNMI0012E: The "{0}" custom property value is not of the correct format. Default value of {1} is used instead.
Message.Explanation: A value other than an integer number is specified as the custom property value.
Message.UserResponse: Specify an integer number as the value for the custom property.

Message.MsgText: bad.response.from.remote.agent=XNMI0004E: Bad response from remote agent: {0}
Message.Explanation: An unexpected response is received from the remote agent.
Message.UserResponse: If the remote agent is supplied by IBM, report the error to IBM support.

Message.MsgText: remote.agent.port.invalid=XNMI0003E: Remote agent port number "{0}" is invalid. Default port number {1} used instead.
Message.Explanation: A value other than an integer number is specified as the value for the custom property "stats.collector.remote.agent.port".
Message.UserResponse: Specify an integer number as the value for the custom property "stats.collector.remote.agent.port" of the unmanaged node.

Message.MsgText: number.of.cpus.invalid=XNMI0002E: NumberOfCPUs "{0}" received from remote agent is not of the correct format. Default value of {1} is used instead.
Message.Explanation: A value other than an integer number is received from the remote agent as the number of CPUs running in the remote node.
Message.UserResponse: If the remote agent is supplied by IBM, report the error to IBM support.

Message.MsgText: error.encountered.loading.plugin=XNMI0013E: An error was encountered loading the class "{0}". Cause: {1}.
Message.Explanation: The system was not able to load the named class because of the problem identified in the message.
Message.UserResponse: Remedy the problem according to the message. If the cause of the problem is ClassNotFoundException, make sure that the name of the class is spelled correctly and that the class is in the Application Server classpath.

Message.MsgText: service.started.successfully=XNMI0010I: The external node stats service started successfully.
Message.Explanation: The external node stats service started successfully and is available to service requests.

Message.MsgText: stats.collector.impl.class.invalid=XNMI0014E: Class "{0}" identified by the custom property "{1}" does not implement the "{2}" interface.
Message.Explanation: The class named by the particular custom property of the unmanaged node must implements the specified interface.
Message.UserResponse: Specify the correct class or remove the custom property from the unmanaged node so the system will use a default class for this operation.
